{
  "description": "R2c L3 event-graph goldens — ground truth for the al-sem → Rust differential harness. Each <fixture>.l3eg.golden.json is the ALLOWLISTED event-graph projection of a RESOLVED SemanticModel, READ post-resolve / pre-summary (`indexWorkspace` → `resolveModel` ONCE; the dump NEVER re-runs buildEventGraph — it READS model.eventGraph). EventSymbols (publishers + synthesized maybe/unknown) in stable id form (StableEventId from the EventSymbol via the rawEventId→stableEventId last-wins map; publisherObjectId stable/opaque via the dumb /→: replace; publisherRoutineId as StableRoutineId; signatureHash verbatim incl. the synthesized sha256Hex(RAW eventId)). EventEdges (subscribers, open-world: every parseable subscriber → exactly one edge) with eventId mapped THROUGH the map, subscriberRoutineId as StableRoutineId, subscriberAppId, resolution (resolved iff a REAL indexed publisher produces the eventId; maybe for an existing target with no real publisher; unknown for a target object not in indexed source). See scripts/r2c-l3eg-projection.ts.",
  "capturePoint": "post-resolve/pre-summary (indexWorkspace → resolveModel ONCE; READ model.eventGraph, no rebuild)",
  "note": "R2c reads the FIXED (al-sem ≥9eb9c55) event graph: `resolved` consults realPublisherEventIds (NOT eventById), so a 2nd+ subscriber to an unindexed event on an existing object stays `maybe`. EXCLUDED (later gates / separate pass): call graph (R2b), typedEdges (L4/R3), RoutineSummary (L4), coverage/gaps (R2d), publish capability facts (L4-injected — R3/L4). The 'unknown' sentinel publisherObjectId (`unknown:<type>:0:<targetRef>`) is an OPAQUE comparison id — Rust must string-replace, NOT parse. Cross-app event targets (.app deps) → R2.5.",
  "alSemGitSha": "b3ea1a0fc6d6056d46859416d085ab62c0f44006",
  "treeSitterAlTag": "v2.5.2-shim",
